Redirected diagnostic output to stderr across scripts.

Changed informational and debug messages to print to stderr (>&2) instead of stdout.
This follows Unix conventions where:
- stdout: Command output/results (piped to other commands)
- stderr: Diagnostic info, errors, debug messages (not piped)

Changes in git-arch:
- Invalid option message
- List mode confirmation message

Changes in git-resolve:
- Debug output for argument parsing at multiple stages
- Makes stdout clean for actual command output/results

This separation allows scripts to be used in pipelines without diagnostic noise.

/Claude-haiku@4.5
